content:
Lets connect to our database. First we need to add respective JDBC driver. for eg if we need to connect to postgres we need to add
&lt;dependency&gt; &lt;groupId&gt;org.postgresql&lt;/groupId&gt; &lt;artifactId&gt;postgresql&lt;/artifactId&gt; &lt;version&gt;${postgresql.version}&lt;/version&gt; &lt;/dependency&gt;Next, We need configure SQLComponents to connect to our database instance. we should create file named sql-components.yml with below details
# Connection Details name: Sample url: &#34;jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/sampledb&#34; userName: &#34;user&#34; password: &#34;password&#34; schemaName: &#34;sampledb&#34; # Mapping Logic rootPackage: &#34;com.example&#34;
